# Trivy IaC ignore file — global rule suppression (passed to trivy-action via
# the `trivyignores:` input). Each entry has a rationale; please keep them in
# sync with the inline comments above the affected resource so the "why" is
# visible at the call site too.
#
# Inline `# trivy:ignore:<id>` comments were tried first but didn't parse
# reliably with trivy 0.70 + this action's invocation; the file-based form
# below is the documented, dependable escape hatch.

# AVD-KSV-0109 — ConfigMap stores secrets
# False positive on apps/homepage/configmap.yaml. The `password:` keys hold
# homepage template placeholders ({{HOMEPAGE_VAR_*_PASSWORD}}) that are
# substituted from the SOPS-encrypted secret.enc.yaml at runtime.
KSV0109

# AVD-KSV-0014 — Container should set readOnlyRootFilesystem
# Deferred on apps/homepage/manifests.yaml. gethomepage's Next.js runtime
# writes within /app/.next at startup; locking it down requires explicit
# emptyDir mounts and a verification pass. Mitigations in place: runAsNonRoot,
# drop ALL caps, allowPrivilegeEscalation=false, seccomp=RuntimeDefault.
# TODO: revisit when we add /tmp + /app/.next/cache emptyDir mounts.
KSV0014

# AVD-KSV-0118 — Workload using default security context
# Legitimate root on platform/observability/monitoring/kube-prometheus-stack/
# etcd-cert-syncer.yaml (Job + CronJob). Both mount /etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/
# from the control-plane host (hostPath) to copy etcd client certs. Reading
# those files requires root. Confined to control-plane nodes by nodeSelector
# + tolerations.
KSV0118

# AVD-DS-0002 — Dockerfile missing USER directive
# Bare-metal Docker container on the monitoring-server reverse-proxy
# (infrastructure/services/monitoring-server/configuration/reverse-proxy/
# Dockerfile). Uses upstream nginx:latest which runs as root to bind ports
# 80/443 directly on the host. TODO: switch to nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged
# with port mapping when the monitoring-server config is next revisited.
DS0002
